│ The user wants me to fix a crash in the LLVM SLP vectorizer.                                                                                                                             │
│ The crash is an assertion failure: `I1 == PoisonMaskElem && "Expected unused subvectors mask"' failed.` in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp:10936`.                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The backtrace indicates the crash happens during cost estimation for vectorization, specifically in `ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize`. This function is building a shuffle mask to        │
│ estimate the cost of a shuffle operation. The assertion fails because it tries to write to a mask element that has already been written. This suggests that two different scalar values  │
│ are being mapped to the same lane of a vector, which should not happen.                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The reproducer IR has a complex control flow graph with many PHI nodes. The issue is likely related to how the SLP vectorizer handles values coming from PHI nodes, especially when      │
│ different PHI nodes are being vectorized together.                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Looking at the code around the assertion in `ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize`:                                                                                                            │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ // llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                                                                                       │
│ ...                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ 10934         int &I1 = Mask[I];                                                                                                                                                         │
│ 10935         // TODO: Should be undef.                                                                                                                                                  │
│ 10936         assert(I1 == PoisonMaskElem && "Expected unused subvectors mask");                                                                                                         │
│ 10937         I1 = UndefMaskElem;                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ...                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ 10946         int &I1 = Mask[I];                                                                                                                                                         │
│ 10947         assert(I1 == PoisonMaskElem && "Expected unused subvectors mask");                                                                                                         │
│ 10948         I1 = SubVecOffsets[Idx] + I;                                                                                                                                               │
│ ...                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ The assertion `I1 == PoisonMaskElem` ensures that each lane in the shuffle mask is only assigned once. `PoisonMaskElem` is the initial value for all mask elements.                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The problem is likely in how the vectorizer decides which scalar instructions to group together. In the case of PHI nodes, if two PHIs are part of the same vectorization candidate but  │
│ have different incoming values for the same predecessor basic block, this can lead to conflicts.                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ A common pattern for fixing such issues in the SLP vectorizer is to add checks to prevent illegal or conflicting groupings. In this case, when considering vectorizing a group of PHI    │
│ nodes, we should ensure that for any given predecessor block, all PHIs in the group have the same incoming value. If they have different incoming values, they cannot be part of the     │
│ same vectorized shuffle, as it would require shuffling different scalars into the same lane depending on which PHI is considered.                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
