│ The core issue is that `PHIHandler` assumes all PHIs in the group have the same incoming block structure as the first PHI. The correct check is to ensure that for every incoming edge   │
│ of the main PHI, all other PHIs in the group also have an incoming edge from that same predecessor block.                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will now implement this more precise check. I'll iterate through the incoming blocks of the main PHI and for each block, I'll check if all other PHIs in the group have an incoming    │
│ value from that block. `PHINode::getBasicBlockIndex` can be used for this. It returns -1 if the block is not a predecessor.                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This is the logic:                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ 1.  In `buildTree_rec`, `case Instruction::PHI:`.                                                                                                                                        │
│ 2.  Get the main PHI: `auto *PH = cast<PHINode>(VL[0]);`.                                                                                                                                │
